&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.2em;"&gt;‚ö°Ô∏è&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="text-transform: uppercase;    font-weight: 600; font-size: 1.2em;"&gt;IN BRIEF&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;üîé &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180568/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;A quick explainer to WCAG 3.0&lt;/a&gt;, the next generation of the W3C's accessibility standards. It's all work in progress, with a draft candidate recommendation not expected till¬†2027.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚ú® If you need some design inspiration, &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180509/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;this site brings together a collection of nice HTML UI components&lt;/a&gt; that are &lt;em&gt;'ready to drop into your next project'&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;‚úÖ Version 28 of developer browser Polypane &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180507/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;is now available&lt;/a&gt;, introducing a new Environments feature, improved Elements panel, and more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ü§î &lt;a href="https://frontendfoc.us/link/180508/rss" style=" color: #D94306; font-weight: 600;"&gt;How do browsers work?&lt;/a&gt; A high-level overview of how browsers work in¬†practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
